        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 8:02PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 802 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Peetz, or 22 miles north of Sterling, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Peetz, Crook, Proctor and Twin Buttes.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Prepare for sudden gusty winds. Secure loose objects and move to a
safe shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
